com.whitepages.proapi.api.response

Class Response<T extends Entity>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.whitepages.proapi.api.response.Response<T>

  • public class Response<T extends Entity>
extends java.lang.Object

    The Response is the root object for data returned from queries performed via the Client find methods.

    The key properties of a Response are:

    • The results (via getResults()): The list of the Entity instances found for the corresponding query,
    • The response messages (via getResponseMessages()): A collection of Message instances pertaining to the response; these may include error conditions.

    Response success can be determined via the isSuccess() and isFailure() accessors. In the event of a failure response, the cause of the failure is recorded in the response messages.
